Company description:
About Us:
At TerryWhite Chemmart (TWCM), we are dedicated to delivering frontline healthcare, ensuring every Australian has easy access to expert health advice and outstanding pharmaceutical care.
Our vision is to build a better future for Australian pharmacy, and we need passionate individuals like you to help us achieve this goal.
TWCM is a division of EBOS Healthcare and part of the EBOS Group. With almost 5,000 employees in 115 locations across Australia, New Zealand, and Southeast Asia, EBOS Group is the largest and most diversified Australasian marketer, wholesaler and distributor of healthcare, medical and pharmaceutical products. It is also a leading marketer and distributor of recognised animal care brands.
EBOS Group is publicly listed on the New Zealand and Australian stock exchanges.
Job description:
TWC is seeking a
Group Reporting Analyst
with a passion and love of reporting to join their finance team based out of our Brisbane Support Centre.
Reporting to the Commercial and Data Services Manager, you will be responsible for the delivery of effective & high-quality reporting and analysis as well as supporting internal stakeholder data expectations through provision of accurate, timely and detailed data analytics to enhance data driven decision making.
What's exciting about this role is that you will gain exposure to all areas of the business including Commercial, Merchandise, Marketing and Operations Business units, therefore your ability to build strong working relationships, work collaboratively with diverse teams and communicate effectively at all levels will be key to success.
What you will do:
Apply your strong data interpretation skills to generate business insights and create visualisations and dashboards to present data effectively to stakeholders;
Work with stakeholders to translate business needs into actionable reports to drive business outcomes;
Provide technical support on visualisation tools and systems;
Update and maintain existing reporting standards;
Increase the quality and ease of access to information used for decision making across the business.
What we are looking for:
A strong passion for bulding reports and dashboards for end users;
Prior experience working in a reporting role or Data Analyst within the retail industry highly regarded;
Sound knowledge of data manipulation for reporting outcomes;
Previous exposure and use of Power BI including ability to implement DAX language;
Exposure to CRM and/or customer data and modelling advantageous but not essential;
Experience building and maintaining dashboards & reports to clearly communicate data insights.
We offer:
